---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — UniversityX"
  description="Learn how UniversityX collects, uses, and protects your personal information."
>
  <div class="bg-[#FBF8F1]">
    <Navbar />
  </div>

  <main class="bg-[#FBF8F1] min-h-screen">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">

      <h1 class="font-['Playfair_Display'] text-4xl font-bold text-[#1A0533] mb-3">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[#1A0533]/50 mb-12">Last updated: May 5, 2026</p>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-[#1A0533]/80 space-y-10">

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#1A0533] mb-3">1. Who We Are</h2>
          <p>
            UniversityX ("we", "us", or "our") operates the website at
            <a href="https://universityx.app" class="text-[#BB39B4] underline underline-offset-2">https://universityx.app</a>
            — an online learning platform that connects learners with instructors for in-demand skills courses and workshops.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            For any privacy-related questions, contact us at:
            <a href="mailto:hello@universityx.app" class="text-[#BB39B4] underline underline-offset-2">hello@universityx.app</a>
            or
            <a href="mailto:officialuniversityx@gmail.com" class="text-[#BB39B4] underline underline-offset-2">officialuniversityx@gmail.com</a>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#1A0533] mb-3">2. Information We Collect</h2>
          <p>We collect information in the following ways:</p>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-[#1A0533] mt-5 mb-2">a) Information you provide directly</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
            <li>Full name</li>
            <li>Email address</li>
            <li>WhatsApp phone number (when you join our community)</li>
            <li>Messages or enquiries you send via our contact form</li>
            <li>Information submitted when applying to teach on the platform</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-[#1A0533] mt-5 mb-2">b) Information from Google Sign-In</h3>
          <p>
            When you choose to sign in with Google, we receive basic profile information from your Google account, including your name, email address, and profile picture. We use this solely to create and manage your UniversityX account. We do not access your Google Drive, Gmail, or any other Google services.
          </p>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-[#1A0533] mt-5 mb-2">c) Usage and analytics data</h3>
          <p>
            We use Google Analytics and PostHog to collect anonymised data about how visitors use our site — including pages visited, time spent, and general geographic location. This data does not personally identify you.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#1A0533] mb-3">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 mt-2">
            <li>Create and manage your account on UniversityX</li>
            <li>Enrol you in courses or workshops you sign up for</li>
            <li>Send you relevant updates, course announcements, and community invitations</li>
            <li>Respond to your enquiries and support requests</li>
            <li>Improve the platform based on how it is used</li>
            <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties for marketing purposes.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#1A0533] mb-3">4. Google OAuth & Limited Use Disclosure</h2>
          <p>
            UniversityX's use of information received from Google APIs adheres to the
            <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy" class="text-[#BB39B4] underline underline-offset-2" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google API Services User Data Policy</a>,
            including the Limited Use requirements.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">Specifically:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 mt-2">
            <li>We only use data obtained via Google Sign-In to authenticate you and provide access to your UniversityX account.</li>
            <li>We do not use this data to serve you personalised advertising.</li>
            <li>We do not allow humans to read your Google data unless you have explicitly given us permission, it is necessary for security purposes, or we are required to do so by law.</li>
            <li>We do not transfer this data to third parties except as necessary to provide the service.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#1A0533] mb-3">5. Data Storage & Security</h2>
          <p>
            Your data is stored securely using PocketBase, our backend database provider. We take reasonable technical and organisational measures to protect your information against unauthorised access, loss, or misuse. However, no method of internet transmission is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#1A0533] mb-3">6. Data Retention</h2>
          <p>
            We retain your personal information for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide you with our services. You may request deletion of your account and associated data at any time by contacting us at
            <a href="mailto:hello@universityx.app" class="text-[#BB39B4] underline underline-offset-2">hello@universityx.app</a>
            or <a href="mailto:officialuniversityx@gmail.com" class="text-[#BB39B4] underline underline-offset-2">officialuniversityx@gmail.com</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#1A0533] mb-3">7. Cookies</h2>
          <p>
            We use cookies and similar tracking technologies for analytics and to remember your preferences. You can disable cookies in your browser settings, though this may affect some functionality of the site.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#1A0533] mb-3">8. Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p>We work with the following third-party services that may process your data:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 mt-2">
            <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> — website traffic analytics</li>
            <li><strong>PostHog</strong> — product analytics and event tracking</li>
            <li><strong>Google OAuth</strong> — authentication</li>
            <li><strong>WhatsApp</strong> — community communication</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-2">Each of these services has its own privacy policy governing their use of your data.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#1A0533] mb-3">9. Your Rights</h2>
          <p>You have the right to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 mt-2">
            <li>Access the personal data we hold about you</li>
            <li>Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
            <li>Withdraw consent for communications at any time</li>
            <li>Lodge a complaint with a relevant data protection authority</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-2">To exercise any of these rights, email us at <a href="mailto:hello@universityx.app" class="text-[#BB39B4] underline underline-offset-2">hello@universityx.app</a> or <a href="mailto:officialuniversityx@gmail.com" class="text-[#BB39B4] underline underline-offset-2">officialuniversityx@gmail.com</a>.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#1A0533] mb-3">10. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Our platform is not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us so we can delete it promptly.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#1A0533] mb-3">11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the "Last updated" date at the top of this page. Continued use of UniversityX after any changes constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#1A0533] mb-3">12. Contact Us</h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:
          </p>
          <address class="not-italic mt-2 text-[#1A0533]/80 space-y-1">
            <p><strong>UniversityX</strong></p>
            <p>Email: <a href="mailto:hello@universityx.app" class="text-[#BB39B4] underline underline-offset-2">hello@universityx.app</a> / <a href="mailto:officialuniversityx@gmail.com" class="text-[#BB39B4] underline underline-offset-2">officialuniversityx@gmail.com</a></p>
            <p>Website: <a href="https://universityx.app" class="text-[#BB39B4] underline underline-offset-2">https://universityx.app</a></p>
          </address>
        </section>

      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
